Build for a single platform
---------------------------

1. Run the unix_setup script with the following arguments, to create a
   build directory:
	- Source directory
	- OS name
	- optional gcc compiler flags

   Example: % ../alsp_src/unix/unix_setup ../alsp_src hpux -g -DINTCONSTR

   The OS option can also be "all", which creates build directories for
   all the supported Unix OSs.

2. Enter the created build directory and execute make.

   Example: % make

	This will build alspro_b and alspro.

3. To build alsdev:

	- Perform cvs checkout alsdev (or equivalent) at same level as these build dirs;

	- Link /netwk/dakota/ALS_Software/ALS_Packages/Tcl-Tk_Interface/Tcl-Tk_Interface_1.03/
		(or equivalent) to "tcltk_interface" at the same level as these build dirs; 
   
	- In the build dir(s), perform:

		make alsdev


Build for multiple platforms at the ALS Office
----------------------------------------------

1. Run the unix_setup script with the following arguments, to create build
   directories for all the supported Unix OSs:
	- Source directory
	- OS name "all"
	- optional gcc compiler flags

   Example: % ../alsp_src/unix/unix_setup ../alsp_src all -g -DINTCONSTR

2. Run the build_all shell script with the following arguments, to perform
   makes on all available Unix OSs:
	-parent of build directories
	-make options

   Example: % ../alsp_src/unix/build_all /apache/builds libalspro.a

   Error messages printed on the standard error stream will be stored in a
   files named os.err, where os is the name of the Unix OS.

Build Installer
---------------

To create an installer for Unix system, an install configuration file
called "install_components" must be created in the build's parent directory.

The install_components file defines paths to all the standard components
of the ALS Prolog system that are stored outside for alsp_src.  See the
example install_components file below.

Once the install_components file is set up, execute make (or build all) with
the target installer

Examples: % make installer
          
	  % ../alsp_src/unix/build_all /apache/builds installer

Example install_components file
-------------------------------

TCL_DIR=../../../../../tcltk_interface

ODBC_DIR=../../../odbc

WINDOW_DIR=../../../x_motif

FOREIGN_SDK_DIR=/dakota/als_foreign_sdks/UNIX_Foreign_SDK

EXAMPLES_DIR=/dakota/examples

MANUAL_DIR=/dakota/als_man/als_man.pdf/guide


